@page "/AboutUs"

<PageTitle>About Us</PageTitle>

<MudContainer MaxWidth="MaxWidth.Large" Class="mt-6 mb-10">

  <MudText Typo="Typo.h3" GutterBottom="true">
    About Backstage
</MudText>

<MudPaper Class="pa-6 mb-6">

    <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" GutterBottom="true">
        About the Chicago International Puppet Festival
    </MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-4">
        Backstage is an inventory management and organizational platform
        developed for the Chicago International Puppet Theater Festival.
    </MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" GutterBottom="true">
        The Problem
    </MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-4">
        Relying on dated spreadsheets and group chats to track merchandise
        quantity and location can be inefficient during a busy festival season.
        The Puppet Festival needed a centralized system to accurately manage
        inventory, locations, and merchandise availability in real time.
    </MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" GutterBottom="true">
        The Opportunity
    </MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-4">
        With our team’s combined development and design expertise, Backstage
        was created to modernize inventory tracking and improve festival
        organization through a single streamlined platform.
    </MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.h5" GutterBottom="true">
        Design Challenge
    </MudText>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
        The challenge was designing a platform that is easy to navigate,
        scalable for festival operations, and accessible for both technical
        and non-technical users.
    </MudText>

</MudPaper>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.h4" GutterBottom="true">
        Key Features
    </MudText>

    <MudPaper Class="pa-6 mb-6">
       <MudList T="string" Dense="true">
    <MudListItem>Inventory Management</MudListItem>
    <MudListItem>Catalog Organization</MudListItem>
    <MudListItem>Location Tracking</MudListItem>
    <MudListItem>Sales Management</MudListItem>
    <MudListItem>Box Packing & Accepting</MudListItem>
    <MudListItem>Alerts & Notifications</MudListItem>
</MudList>
    </MudPaper>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.h4" GutterBottom="true">
        How To Use Backstage
    </MudText>

    <MudPaper Class="pa-6 mb-6">
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            1. Register and confirm your account using email authentication.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            2. Login to access the dashboard and management tools.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            3.Navigate through inventory, sales, locations, and catalog tools using the sidebar.
        </MudText>

        <MudText Typo="Typo.body1">
            4. Use analytics and notifications tools to monitor festival operations.
        </MudText>
    </MudPaper>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.h4" GutterBottom="true">
        Documentation & Resources
    </MudText>

    <MudPaper Class="pa-6 mb-6">
       <MudButton Variant="Variant.Filled"
           Color="Color.Primary"
           Href="https://docs.google.com/document/d/1nF95N21lJMgjo-Bfp0SRCi45RWpoAMTdq1H7tb_-SFo/edit?usp=sharing"
           Target="_blank">
    Open Team Documentation
</MudButton>
    </MudPaper>

    <MudText Typo="Typo.h4" GutterBottom="true">
        Credits
    </MudText>

    <MudPaper Class="pa-6 mb-6">
      <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
      Backstage was developed by student developers and designers
      at Columbia College Chicago in partnership with the Chicago International
      Puppet Theater Festival.
</MudText>
    </MudPaper>

</MudContainer>